CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 28, 1953, pg. 30, reads: "'Command Performance' Real-Gone Fun Package; 'Chuck Fly' Flies Right - At 'Command Performance' - When the Program Department of the Centre Avenue YMCA held its third annual 'Command Performance' show at Schenley High School Auditorium Tuesday night as a benefit for the World Service Fund among the top-drawer acts which received loud applause were, left to right: Rummy Bishop, comedian... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Comedian Rummy Bishop holding cane and performing in front of Walt Harper's band, including Nate Harper on saxophone and Jon Morris on trombone, in Schenley High School auditorium for Centre Avenue YMCA annual "Command Performance" show
